  "response": "Here are some pros and cons of using Ruby for mobile app development:\n\nPros of Ruby:\n- Ruby is easy to learn and has clean, readable syntax\n- Good developer productivity\n- Strong community and ecosystem\n- Frameworks like RubyMotion exist for mobile development\n\nCons of Ruby for mobile:\n- Not a native mobile development language\n- Performance can be slower compared to native development\n- Limited mobile-specific libraries\n- Less recommended for complex mobile apps\n- Limited job market for Ruby mobile developers\n\nBetter alternatives:\n- Swift (iOS)\n- Kotlin/Java (Android)\n- React Native (cross-platform)\n- Flutter (cross-platform)\n- Xamarin (cross-platform)\n\nRecommendation:\nUnless you have specific Ruby expertise, I'd suggest using a more mainstream mobile development approach that provides better performance, native capabilities, and broader community support.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on mobile development technologies?",
